As of the census<ref name=census2010/> of 2010, there were 528 people living in the town. There were 194 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] was 98.3% White, 0.4% Black or African American, 0.2% American Indian and Alaska Native, 0.2% from some other race, and 0.9% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 2.1% of the population.

